Australian financial services licensee organisation name - Provide the name of the Australian Financial Services licensee. If the licensee is a company, the legal elements (eg 'Ltd') must be included. Under the Corporations Act 2001 people, partnerships, trustees or companies who carry on a business of providing financial services are required to hold an Australian Financial Services licence (unless they are covered by an exemption or are authorised to provide those financial services as a representative of an entity that holds an AFS licence).
